25|$|The acarajé is a dish {{made from}} peeled black-eyed peas formed <b>into</b> <b>a</b> <b>ball</b> <b>and</b> then deep-fried in dendê (palm oil). Often sold as street food, it is served split {{in half and}} then stuffed with vatapá and caruru. Acarajé is {{typically}} available outside {{of the state of}} Bahia as well, including the markets of Rio de Janeiro.|$|E
