40|$|McDuff and Schlenk {{determined}} when a four-dimensional ellipsoid can be symplectically embedded <b>into</b> <b>a</b> four-dimensional <b>ball,</b> <b>and</b> {{found that}} when the ellipsoid is close to round, the answer is given by an "infinite staircase" determined by the odd-index Fibonacci numbers. We show that this result still holds in higher dimensions when we "stabilize" the embedding problem...|$|R
